Ethel C. JONES, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 22780. United States Court of Appeals Fifth Circuit. April 11, 1966. John Dale Powers, Robert A. Hawthorne, Jr., Baton Rouge, La., for appellant. Gene S. Palmisano, Asst. U. S. Atty., New Orleans, La., Louis C. LaCour, U. S. Atty., for appellee.

Before JONES and BELL, Circuit Judges, and BREWSTER, District Judge.

PER CURIAM:

No error appearing, the judgment of the district court is affirmed. Jones v. United States, 239 F.Supp. 474.

Affirmed.
